The paper proposes a novel unsupervised representation learning model for recovering multi-subspace structures and extracting adaptive locality-preserving salient features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of regularizers and optimization techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also discusses the use of latent low-rank representation models, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
